{{Infobox language |name=Basa-Gumna |altname=Basa Kuta |nativename=Basa-Kaduna |states=[[Nigeria]] |region=[[Chanchaga]] |extinct=by 1987 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo languages|Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Kainji languages|Kainji]] |fam5=[[Basa languages]] |fam6=Kontagora–Gumna |iso3=bsl |glotto=basa1280 |glottorefname=Basa-Gumna }}
'''Basa-Gumna''' is an extinct [[Kainji language]] of [[Nigeria]]. It was spoken in [[Chanchaga]], Niger state, and [[Nasarawa, Nasarawa State|Nasarawa]], near the Basa homeland. Speakers have shifted to Hausa.
