{{Infobox language |name=Esuma |states=[[Ivory Coast]] |extinct=ca. 1800 |ref=linglist |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Kwa languages|Kwa]] |fam4=(unclassified) |iso3=esm |glotto=esum1241 |glottorefname=Esuma |linglist=esm }} '''Esuma''' (Essouma) is an extinct language of uncertain classification within the [[Kwa language|Kwa]] branch of the [[Niger–Congo languages|Niger–Congo]] family, once spoken in the villages of [[Assinie-Mafia|Assinie (Asini) and Mafia]] in [[Ivory Coast]]. The Esuma were vassals of the [[Kingdom of Sanwi|Sanwi]] capital [[Krinjabo]], and shifted to the [[Anyin language|Anyin]] and [[Nzima language|Nzima]] languages.
